    "details": "Axel Mierczuk reports:\n\n> By default, the Redis configuration does not limit the output buffer\n> of normal clients (see client-output-buffer-limit). Therefore, the\n> output buffer can grow unlimitedly over time. As a result, the service\n> is exhausted and the memory is unavailable.\n>\n> When password authentication is enabled on the Redis server, but no\n> password is provided, the client can still cause the output buffer to\n> grow from \\\"NOAUTH\\\" responses until the system will run out of\n> memory.\n",
